article.description: Mondy's 2nd half lifts Oakland past Detroit, 76-69
article.headline: Mondy's 2nd half lifts Oakland past Detroit, 76-69
article.linkText: Mondy's 2nd half lifts Oakland past Detroit, 76-69
article.story: DETROIT -- Duke Mondy drilled a 3-pointer to tie and Travis Bader made another to give Oakland the lead and the Golden Grizzlies closed out Detroit with an 11-1 run for a 76-69 win Saturday. Juwan Howard, Jr.'s jumper with 3:08 left gave Detroit a 68-65 lead, but it was the Titans' final field goal. Detroit (8-10, 1-2 Horizon) led by eight at the half and a Howard jumper pushed the lead to 10 points early in the second half. Mondy scored 15 of his 18 points in the second half and was 4 of 4 from the line with a jumper in the final 19 seconds to secure the win. Corey Petros led the Golden Grizzlies (7-12, 2-2) with 23 points and 13 rebounds. Bader and Kahlil finished with 14 and 12 points, respectively. Howard and Evan Bruinsma had 15 and 14 points, respectively, for Detroit.
